node.text: JC and Henok make time to catch up on their friendship that formed during the first Rate Beer fest and how Omnipollo's intriguing intersection of beer, pop culture and artistic exploration resonates so much with JC. Fast forward today and hear about how @omnipollo beer is available all over the world while at the same time setting down deeper roots in Sweden. We hit refresh on Covered In Puppies, our collaboration DIPA and its drinking beautifully. We miss you Henok & Karl!

Compass was the first release in the series and today, it returns to our coolers! Hopped with American Noble™ Citra and @fourstarfarms Crystal, order cans online now for Pickup and UPS Direct.

node.text:
In August of 2020, we released our take on Black is Beautiful Imperial Stout with our friends at White Lion Brewing as part of an international movement to directly address police brutality and the legal injustices that American people of color face every day.

This project saw participation from over 1,200 breweries in 22 countries, raising much-needed awareness for inequity and funds for organizations that are putting in the work towards equality and inclusion.

The founder of Black is Beautiful is Marcus Baskerville, Owner and Head Brewer at Weathered Souls Brewing. We got to know Marcus through this project and quickly became fond of his lineup of beers, in particular the impressive array of Imperial and Barrel-Aged Stouts that the brewery releases on a regular basis. 

When the opportunity arose to collaborate on a beer together, we noted our shared appreciation for BBQ and fused the storied traditions of pit smoking and stout brewing.

Featuring barley smoked on our Primitive Pit smoker over New England maple and oak, Feed Your Soul.

node.text:
Tomorrow marks the return of an all-time favorite collaboration with our long-time friends at @row34!

As members of @northeastgrains and mutual fans of classic Belgian and French Saison, it was important to both parties that we honor tradition while utilizing local ingredients.

Brewed with 100% @valleymalt and hopped with gorgeous Czech Saaz, we made some thoughtful process tweaks that have brought batch two to new heights.

Nuanced, with layers of complexity, we're picking up notes of cracked white peppercorn, fresh-squeezed lemonade, toasted clove, black tea, and dried hay atop a lively effervescence and dry, crackling finish.

Bottles will be available to order online for Pickup and UPS Direct tomorrow at 9 AM. 7.0% ABV. $8.05/500ml bottle, no limits. Row34 will also have bottles available at their Fort Point and Burlington locations.

Pro-tip: Order a bottle with a dozen Island Creek Oysters and thank us later!

Join us this Saturday, 8/14 from 12-9 PM, as we have the distinct pleasure of welcoming Chef Andrew Samia of San Antonio’s @southbbq to take over our Canton barbecue program for the day.

In addition to their standalone restaurant, South also operates the kitchen at @weatheredsoulsbrewing, owned by our friend Marcus Baskerville, who will just so happen to be in town this weekend!

Andrew and his team will be arriving on Friday to prep an overnight cook, ready to be served for you the following day. Enjoy mouth-watering brisket, ribs, sausage, and more. We have a special beer in the works for you as well. More details to come!

We've long admired @theveilbrewing’s Tastee lineup of "Smoothie-style" Sour Ales. Fruited to ludicrous levels and introducing confectionary elements to the mix, these beers offer a lusciously soft mouthfeel and flavor experience like no other.

For our latest collaboration with our Richmond buds, we took inspiration from Tastee, pairing blueberry, blackberry, and raspberry with just a touch of cinnamon, to achieve a drinking experience reminiscent of summertime berry pie.

Cans of Yummee will be available to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for both Pickup as well as UPS Direct. $22.20/4-pack, limit one case per person.

NOTE: This beer is dairy-free.
